 Declear FILE Pointer Opening file  File type mode table Open file with Error checking   Closing file  Closing file with Error checking    Declear FILE Pointer FILE *MyFile; Here FILE is not C keyword, it is a structure that define in &lt;sthio.h&gt; header file.
Opening file /* Header: &lt;stdio.h&gt; Prototype: FILE *fopen(char*fname, char *made); Return: - a FILE pointer -&gt; if successfully - NULL -&gt; On failure */ MyFile = fopen (“myfile.txt”,”w”); File type mode table: The Legal Values for Mode Mode Meaning ---- ------- &quot;r&quot; Open a text file for reading. &quot;w&quot; Create a text file for writing. &quot;a&quot; Append to a text file. &quot;rb&quot; Open a binary file for reading. &quot;wb&quot; Create a binary file for writing. &quot;ab&quot; Append to a binary file. &quot;r+&quot; Open a text file for read/write. &quot;w+&quot; Create a text file for read/write. &quot;a+&quot; Append or create a text file for read/write. &quot;r+b&quot; Open a binary file for read/write. You may also use &quot;rb+&quot;. &quot;w+b&quot; Create a binary file for read/write. You may also use &quot;wb+&quot;. &quot;a+b&quot; Append or create a binary file for read/write. You may also use &quot;ab+&quot;. Open file with Error checking /* Header: &lt;stdlib.h&gt; Prototype: void exit (int status); */ /* Header: &lt;stdio.h&gt; Macro: #define NULL ((void *)0) */ MyFile = fopen (“myfile.txt”,”w”); if (MyFile == NULL) { printf(&#34;Error opening file
&#34;); exit(1); // or substitute your own error handler } The C library Macro NULL is the value of a null pointer constant. It may be defined as ((void*)0), 0 or 0L depending on the compiler vendor. It&rsquo;s define in &lt;stdio.h&gt; header file.
// This fragment is same as the previes on but more efficient if ((MyFile = fopen(&#34;myfile.txt&#34;, &#34;w&#34;)) == NULL) { printf(&#34;Error opening file
&#34;); exit(1); } Closing file /* Header: &lt;stdio.h&gt; Prototype = int fclose(FILE *fp); Return: - 0 -&gt; if the stream is successfully closed. - EOF or -1 -&gt; On failure */ /* Header: &lt;stdio.h&gt; Macro: #define EOF (-1) */ fclose (MyFile); Closing file with Error checking if (fclose(MyFile) == EOF) { printf(&#34;Error closing destination file.
&#34;); exit(1); }
